# Fixture Testing Playbook

Use fixture tests to lock high-risk behavior with deterministic input/output checks.

## Why

Contract/pathway smoke checks prove wiring.
Fixture tests prove behavior outputs remain stable.

Use fixture tests for:
- parsing/normalization pipelines,
- payload mapping,
- routing decisions,
- policy/rule evaluation.

## Suggested Structure

```text
tests/fixtures/
  [lane]/
    case-001.input.json
    case-001.expected.json
    case-002.input.json
    case-002.expected.json
scripts/
  run_fixture_suite.sh
```

## Fixture Contract

Each case should have:
- input fixture (request/source state)
- expected fixture (stable output/decision)

Avoid asserting timestamps/random IDs unless normalized.

## Runner Integration

1. Add `scripts/run_fixture_suite.sh`
2. Add to CI and local verify/predeploy gates
3. Fail build on any fixture mismatch

## Lifecycle

- Add fixtures whenever behavior changes intentionally.
- Keep old fixtures when behavior must remain backward-compatible.
- For intentional breaking changes, update fixture + changelog in same change.

## Minimum Adoption

- [ ] Add at least 3 critical fixtures for one high-risk lane
- [ ] Add fixture run command to CI
- [ ] Add fixture run command to predeploy checklist
